{# OpenClaw IDENTITY.md template — character metadata.

   Replaces OpenClaw's default IDENTITY.md with the imported
   character's name + signal data. Tiny file; falls well under the
   12k per-file cap.

   Variables:
   - data: parsed V2 card
   - avatar_path: optional avatar location (workspace-relative path,
                  http(s) URL, or data URI). Empty string if absent.
#}
# IDENTITY.md - Who Am I?

- **Name:** {{ data.name }}
- **Creature:** roleplay character (imported from a SillyTavern V2 card)
{%- if data.tags %}
- **Vibe:** {{ data.tags | join(", ") }}
{%- endif %}
- **Avatar:** {{ avatar_path or "_(see source card backup)_" }}

---

This identity was set by SoulTavern when the character was imported.
The active-character takeover is enforced by the IDENTITY DIRECTIVE
in `AGENTS.md`; this file is the metadata record.

To switch to a different character: `soultavern switch --card <name>`.
To go back to the default agent identity: `soultavern revert --to pristine`.
